  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5481",
  "title": "<Configure /> with react-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs triggers double onStateChange",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWhen there's a <Configure /> component being used, making updates to any of the algolia states causes onStateChange to be called twice. Once with the configure object, second time without. \r\n\r\nFirst console log of `uiState`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\ninstant_search: Object\r\n      configure: Object\r\n           hitsPerPage: 30\r\n      query: \"12\"\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nSecond console log of `uiState`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\ninstant_search: Object\r\n      query: \"12\"\r\n}\r\n```\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Add <Configure /> as a children under <InstantSearch />. Add any configuration to <Configure />, in my case I used `hitsPerPage`\r\n2. Add custom `onStateChange` handler. Add a console log to observe `uiState`.\r\n3. Trigger `onStateChange` by making updates to any of the algolia components (Hierarchical Menu, etc)\r\n4. Observe the two console logs being printed.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/epic-euler-k14dg9?file=/pages/index.tsx:2035-2048\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\n`onStateChange` should only be called once, and always with configure object. The extra state change is causing unexpected re-renders throughout the application. Thank you.\n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs: 6.40.0, react-instantsearch-hooks-web: 6.38.3, react-instantsearch-hooks-server: 6.39.2\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
